    "name": "Singapore-style Grilled Black Pepper Crab",
    "description": "Sink your claws into juicy and sweet grilled crab, barbecued to perfection and then coated in a lip-smacking black pepper sauce. Nothing quite says ‘summer’ like it.",
    "prepTime": "PT20M",
    "cookTime": "PT25M",
    "totalTime": "",
    "keywords": "Condiments &amp; Sauces, Crab, Eat with your hands, Grill, Picnic, Restaurant classics, Seafood",
    "recipeYield": "4",
    "recipeCategory": [],
    "recipeCuisine": "",
    "recipeIngredient": [
        "4 blue swimmer crabs, cleaned and cut into pieces",
        "2 tbsp vegetable oil",
        "6 garlic cloves, finely chopped",
        "1 tbsp finely chopped ginger",
        "¼ cup oyster sauce",
        "¼ cup soy sauce",
        "1 tbsp sugar",
        "¼ cup chicken stock",
        "2 tbsp freshly ground black pepper",
        "50g (1.7 oz) butter",
        "4 spring onions, finely sliced"
    ],
    "recipeInstructions": [
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "text": "1.Grill the crab pieces over charcoal or regular barbecue (alternatively cook under a hot oven grill)."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "text": "2.To make the sauce, heat the oil in a saucepan over medium heat. Add the garlic and ginger and cook for half a minute. Then add the oyster sauce, soy sauce, sugar and stock. Simmer for 10 minutes. Then stir through the pepper and butter."
        },
        {
            "@type": "HowToStep",
            "text": "3.Pour the sauce over the grilled crab and scatter over the spring onions."
        }
    ],
